  <bioghist id="aspace_6a09c43422b04651a9a64cd493237288">
    <head>BIOGRAPHICAL NOTE</head>
<p>City planner.</p><p> Adams was involved with the Garden City movement in England, especially Letchworth. He served as Town Planning Advisor to the Canadian government, 1914-1921, and presided over the Regional Plan of New York and Its Environs until its completion in 1931.</p>  </bioghist>
